<br>
I'd suggest grouping when levelling for a spell circle.  You might also prepurchase your spells if you want to be group friendly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ugarbhad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garbhad</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 975<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/22/01 6:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.engin.umich.edu/~rhanold/swedchef/chef7.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enc</span><hr size=1> Ok here are some tips for you.<br>
<br>
At level 16 you have a few options. <br>
you can<br>
A) Solo almost any croc in oasis<br>
B) Head to Highhold and solo any gnoll/orc there<br>
<br>
It's all about spell placement and use. <br>
<br>
level 20-25<br>
Get yourself a few wizard friends, or even shaman friends. Goto Beholder - very underused dungeon...go down to the evil eye pit, and nuke till your heart is content. They have a 7 minute spawn time. I went from 20-25 in 3 days doing this. <br>
<br>
Then the real test...<br>
<br>
get in to dungeon groups - screw this lake of ill omen crap..<br>
<br>
This is where you begin to hone your dungeon abilites.<br>
You have an AE mezz, and a few good single target mezzes. <br>
<br>
If you can get a regular group in to cazic thule or anoother dungeon around that level DO IT.<br>
<br>
I spent less than 3 weeks in CT, i went from 25-40 in that time grouping evry night for 4 hours a night. That's it. <br>
<br>
It may be slower than the outdoor zzones, but i guarantee you will be a better player from it. Put yourself in to every situation imaginable. Trains, dotted mobs, dead tanks, etc...<br>
<br>
This is where you learn. I have a saying that basically goes like this &quot;if an enchanter solos their entire career away, might as well start getting the coffins and a cleric lined up, because you are screwed&quot;<br>
